{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f2f95599-6c19-4aca-b5d6-3a99baa306a4","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. Here are the main approaches:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\n# Install if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Analyze the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Last exception details |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n| `threads` | List all threads |\n| `clrstack -all` | Stacks for all threads |\n\n**Using LLDB** (Linux/macOS) or **WinDbg** (Windows) for deeper native-level analysis.\n\n**Quick start — try this sequence:**\n```\n> pe            # print the exception\n> clrstack      # see the stack trace\n> threads       # check all threads\n```\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file? If so, share the path to the `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"95be9e9c-d31d-4ccf-a5e2-d61e8db40a68","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET app. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So I should NOT invoke that skill.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their crash dump.","outputTokens":376,"requestId":"6003:36F7E:DFA393:103C0FE:69EACBF8"},"id":"d3cd70e2-a3de-49ef-a1ad-67a60c623811","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:48:50.700Z","parentId":"ce573197-dd6c-4aa8-91c3-bc63f463a675"}
